2. Also, Reference No. 2 in the Notification of the General Administration Department, Rule No. As per 2 (2) (c), the Divisional Cadre Allocation Rules, 2021 shall not apply to the cadre of Additional Collector and Additional Collector (Selection Category).

3. For the purposes of regulation of transfers of Maharashtra Government employees and provisions of Section 4 (4) and Section 4 (5) of the Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005, the following officers of the Additional Collector's cadre have been designated in front of their names on administrative grounds / request in Column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.
4. The above mentioned officers are required to join immediately at the place of posting.
The concerned officer should immediately inform the Government by e-mail / post at e.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in 1 as to the date on which he / she appeared at the place of new appointment.

5. Against the officer concerned if it is found that he has not joined the place of transfer before the expiry of the term of office in accordance with the said provisions prescribed under Rule 15 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption, non-acceptance of service and Provisions for periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981.
